  <h1>Whistleblower Award Guides</h1>
  <p><em>Reviewed by our editorial team. Updated May 2026.</em></p>

  <p>Whistleblower programs offer substantial financial awards for individuals who report fraud — but each program has different rules, thresholds, eligibility requirements, and strategic considerations. These guides cover the key programs and the most important decisions potential whistleblowers face.</p>
  <p>All guides are educational materials, not legal advice. Before taking any action under a whistleblower program, consult a qualified whistleblower attorney. Most offer free, confidential initial consultations.</p>

  <h2>How awards work across all programs</h2>
  <h3><a href="/guides/how-whistleblower-awards-work/">How Whistleblower Awards Work</a></h3>
  <p>The core mechanism of percentage-of-sanctions awards, eligibility requirements across all programs, how agencies exercise discretion within the statutory range, the typical timeline from tip to payment, and the tax treatment of awards.</p>

  <h2>The SEC Whistleblower Program in depth</h2>
  <h3><a href="/guides/sec-whistleblower-program/">The SEC Whistleblower Program</a></h3>
  <p>How to submit a Form TCR tip, what qualifies as original information, anonymous submission with attorney representation, the award determination process, and the Dodd-Frank anti-retaliation protections that apply to SEC reporters.</p>

  <h2>False Claims Act qui tam suits</h2>
  <h3><a href="/guides/false-claims-act-qui-tam/">False Claims Act Qui Tam Suits</a></h3>
  <p>How qui tam complaints are filed under seal, the government's 60-day review and extension period, the intervention decision and what it means for award percentage, FCA treble damages and civil penalties, and the major categories of FCA fraud.</p>

  <h2>Common misconceptions</h2>
  <h3><a href="/guides/whistleblower-misconceptions/">Whistleblower Misconceptions</a></h3>
  <p>Five myths that cause potential whistleblowers to underestimate their eligibility or mishandle their submissions: insider status requirements, internal reporting impact, anti-retaliation coverage, tip value thresholds, and submission timing.</p>

